.TH "snd_pcm_stream_lock_irq" 9 "snd_pcm_stream_lock_irq" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
snd_pcm_stream_lock_irq \- Lock the PCM stream
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" snd_pcm_stream_lock_irq
.BI "(struct snd_pcm_substream *substream "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "substream" 12
PCM substream
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This locks the PCM stream like \fBsnd_pcm_stream_lock\fP and disables the local
IRQ (only when nonatomic is false).  In nonatomic case, this is identical
as \fBsnd_pcm_stream_lock\fP.
